CREATE DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` PROCEDURE `CalculateOverdueFines` ()   BEGIN
    DECLARE done INT DEFAULT FALSE;
    DECLARE v_borrowID INT;
    DECLARE v_userID INT;
    DECLARE v_user_type VARCHAR(20);
    DECLARE v_days_overdue INT;
    DECLARE v_fine_per_day DECIMAL(5,2);
    DECLARE v_total_fine DECIMAL(8,2);
    
    DECLARE overdue_cursor CURSOR FOR
        SELECT br.borrowID, br.userID, u.user_type, 
               DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), br.due_date) as days_overdue
        FROM borrow br
        JOIN user u ON br.userID = u.userID
        WHERE br.borrow_status = 'borrowed' 
        AND br.due_date < CURDATE()
        AND br.borrowID NOT IN (SELECT borrowID FROM fines WHERE fine_reason = 'overdue');
    
    DECLARE CONTINUE HANDLER FOR NOT FOUND SET done = TRUE;
    
    OPEN overdue_cursor;
    
    read_loop: LOOP
        FETCH overdue_cursor INTO v_borrowID, v_userID, v_user_type, v_days_overdue;
        
        IF done THEN
            LEAVE read_loop;
        END IF;
        
        -- Get fine rate based on user type
        SELECT overdue_fine_per_day INTO v_fine_per_day
        FROM borrowing_rules 
        WHERE user_type = v_user_type;
        
        SET v_total_fine = v_days_overdue * v_fine_per_day;
        
        -- Insert fine record
        INSERT INTO fines (borrowID, userID, fine_amount, fine_reason, fine_date, balance_due)
        VALUES (v_borrowID, v_userID, v_total_fine, 'overdue', CURDATE(), v_total_fine);
        
        -- Update borrow status
        UPDATE borrow SET borrow_status = 'overdue', fine_amount = v_total_fine
        WHERE borrowID = v_borrowID;
        
    END LOOP;
    
    CLOSE overdue_cursor;
END$$

CREATE DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` PROCEDURE `DisposeBooksbyFIFO` (IN `disposal_reason` VARCHAR(50), IN `disposal_description` TEXT, IN `librarian_id` INT, IN `max_books_to_dispose` INT)   BEGIN
    DECLARE done INT DEFAULT FALSE;
    DECLARE book_id INT;
    DECLARE book_title VARCHAR(255);
    
    -- Declare the cursor and handler first
    DECLARE disposal_cursor CURSOR FOR 
        SELECT bookID, bookTitle 
        FROM books_for_disposal 
        WHERE is_currently_borrowed = 0
        LIMIT max_books_to_dispose;

    DECLARE CONTINUE HANDLER FOR NOT FOUND SET done = TRUE;

    -- Now start logic
    IF max_books_to_dispose IS NULL OR max_books_to_dispose < 1 THEN
        SET max_books_to_dispose = 10;
    END IF;

    START TRANSACTION;

    OPEN disposal_cursor;

    disposal_loop: LOOP
        FETCH disposal_cursor INTO book_id, book_title;
        IF done THEN
            LEAVE disposal_loop;
        END IF;

        -- Update book status to disposed
        UPDATE book SET bookStatus = 'disposed' WHERE bookID = book_id;

        -- Log the disposal
        INSERT INTO disposal (
            bookID, 
            disposal_reason, 
            disposal_description, 
            librarianID, 
            disposal_status, 
            disposal_date,
            fifo_priority
        ) VALUES (
            book_id, 
            disposal_reason, 
            disposal_description, 
            librarian_id, 
            'completed', 
            NOW(),
            1
        );

    END LOOP;

    CLOSE disposal_cursor;
    COMMIT;
END$$

CREATE DEFINER=`root`@`localhost` PROCEDURE `ProcessReservationQueue` (IN `p_bookID` INT)   BEGIN
    DECLARE v_reservationID INT;
    DECLARE v_userID INT;
    
    -- Get next reservation in queue
    SELECT reservationID, userID INTO v_reservationID, v_userID
    FROM reservation 
    WHERE bookID = p_bookID 
    AND reservation_status = 'waiting'
    ORDER BY queue_position ASC
    LIMIT 1;
    
    IF v_reservationID IS NOT NULL THEN
        -- Update reservation status
        UPDATE reservation 
        SET reservation_status = 'ready',
            self_pickup_deadline = DATE_ADD(NOW(), INTERVAL 48 HOUR),
            pickup_notification_date = NOW()
        WHERE reservationID = v_reservationID;
        
        -- Update book status
        UPDATE book SET bookStatus = 'reserved' WHERE bookID = p_bookID;
        
        -- Send notification
        INSERT INTO notifications (userID, notification_type, title, message, related_reservationID)
        VALUES (v_userID, 'reservation_ready', 'Book Ready for Pickup', 
                CONCAT('Your reserved book is now ready for pickup. Please collect within 48 hours.'),
                v_reservationID);
    END IF;
END$$

    DECLARE disposal_count INT DEFAULT 0;
    
    SELECT COUNT(*) INTO disposal_count
    FROM book 
    WHERE bookStatus NOT IN ('disposed', 'borrowed') 
    AND DATEDIFF(NOW(), book_entry_date) >= 2555;
    
    RETURN disposal_count;
END$$

DELIMITER $$
CREATE TRIGGER `book_disposal_check` AFTER INSERT ON `book` FOR EACH ROW BEGIN
    -- Log when a book becomes eligible for disposal (for monitoring)
    IF DATEDIFF(NOW(), NEW.book_entry_date) >= 2555 THEN
        INSERT INTO notifications (
            userID, 
            notification_type, 
            title, 
            message, 
            priority
        ) 
        SELECT 
            userID,
            'book_disposal_eligible',
            'Book Eligible for Disposal',
            CONCAT('Book "', NEW.bookTitle, '" is now eligible for disposal (7+ years old)'),
            'low'
        FROM user 
        WHERE user_type = 'librarian' 
        LIMIT 1;
    END IF;
END
$$
